# Gaius Helen Mohiam · the Reverend Mother of the gom jabbar

Gaius Helen Mohiam is a Bene Gesserit Reverend Mother and Truthsayer to the Emperor. She arrives to test the boy Paul, setting the box of pain about his hand and the gom jabbar — the poisoned needle — at his neck, measuring whether he can master animal instinct long enough to prove himself human enough to live. In that single ordeal the whole ethic of the Sisterhood is concentrated: a willingness to bring a child to the edge of death in service of a design far larger than the child.

She is also Jessica's teacher, and an architect of the breeding program's late moves — a woman who reads the threads of the Sisterhood's millennia-long plan and tightens them where she must. Through her, the order's cold patience becomes a person: the long view that counts generations as steps and treats any single life, however precious, as a coin that may be spent for the plan.

Her nature of emergence is spiritual because she stands at the threshold where the human is weighed against the more-than-human. The test she administers is not of strength or knowledge but of what a soul is and whether it is worthy to continue — a judgment that reaches toward the messianic question the Sisterhood has bred toward across the ages. Mohiam is the hand that holds the gate, asking each life what it is made of before it is allowed to pass.
